frDlcmiTable.name: frDlcmiTable
frDlcmiTable.reference: Draft American National Standard T1.617-1991, Annex D
frDlcmiTable.description: The Parameters for the Data Link Connection Management Interface for the frame relay service on this interface.

frDlcmiEntry.name: frDlcmiEntry
frDlcmiEntry.description: The Parameters for a particular Data Link Con- nection Management Interface.

frDlcmiIfIndex.name: frDlcmiIfIndex
frDlcmiIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the corresponding ifEn- try.

frDlcmiState.name: frDlcmiState
frDlcmiState.description: This variable states which Data Link Connec- tion Management scheme is active (and by impli- cation, what DLCI it uses) on the Frame Relay interface.

frDlcmiAddress.name: frDlcmiAddress
frDlcmiAddress.description: This variable states which address format is in use on the Frame Relay interface.

frDlcmiAddressLen.name: frDlcmiAddressLen
frDlcmiAddressLen.description: This variable states which address length in octets. In the case of Q922 format, the length indicates the entire length of the address in- cluding the control portion.

frDlcmiPollingInterval.name: frDlcmiPollingInterval
frDlcmiPollingInterval.reference: Draft American National Standard T1.617-1991, Section D.7 Timer T391.
frDlcmiPollingInterval.description: This is the number of seconds between succes- sive status enquiry messages.

frDlcmiFullEnquiryInterval.name: frDlcmiFullEnquiryInterval
frDlcmiFullEnquiryInterval.reference: Draft American National Standard T1.617-1991, Section D.7 Counter N391.
frDlcmiFullEnquiryInterval.description: Number of status enquiry intervals that pass before issuance of a full status enquiry mes- sage.

frDlcmiErrorThreshold.name: frDlcmiErrorThreshold
frDlcmiErrorThreshold.reference: Draft American National Standard T1.617-1991, Section D.5.1 Counter N392.
frDlcmiErrorThreshold.description: This is the maximum number of unanswered Status Enquiries the equipment shall accept be- fore declaring the interface down.

frDlcmiMonitoredEvents.name: frDlcmiMonitoredEvents
frDlcmiMonitoredEvents.reference: Draft American National Standard T1.617-1991, Section D.5.2 Counter N393.
frDlcmiMonitoredEvents.description: This is the number of status polling intervals over which the error threshold is counted. For example, if within 'MonitoredEvents' number of events the station receives 'ErrorThreshold' number of errors, the interface is marked as down.

frDlcmiMaxSupportedVCs.name: frDlcmiMaxSupportedVCs
frDlcmiMaxSupportedVCs.description: The maximum number of Virtual Circuits allowed for this interface. Usually dictated by the Frame Relay network. In response to a SET, if a value less than zero or higher than the agent's maximal capability is configured, the agent should respond bad- Value

frDlcmiMulticast.name: frDlcmiMulticast
frDlcmiMulticast.description: This indicates whether the Frame Relay inter- face is using a multicast service.

frCircuitTable.name: frCircuitTable
frCircuitTable.description: A table containing information about specific Data Link Connection Identifiers and corresponding virtual circuits.

frCircuitEntry.name: frCircuitEntry
frCircuitEntry.description: The information regarding a single Data Link Connection Identifier.

frCircuitIfIndex.name: frCircuitIfIndex
frCircuitIfIndex.description: The ifIndex Value of the ifEntry this virtual circuit is layered onto.

frCircuitDlci.name: frCircuitDlci
frCircuitDlci.reference: Draft American National Standard T1.618-1991, Section 3.3.6
frCircuitDlci.description: The Data Link Connection Identifier for this virtual circuit.

frCircuitState.name: frCircuitState
frCircuitState.description: Indicates whether the particular virtual cir- cuit is operational. In the absence of a Data Link Connection Management Interface, virtual circuit entries (rows) may be created by set- ting virtual circuit state to 'active', or deleted by changing Circuit state to 'invalid'. Whether or not the row actually disappears is left to the implementation, so this object may actually read as 'invalid' for some arbitrary length of time. It is also legal to set the state of a virtual circuit to 'inactive' to temporarily disable a given circuit.

frCircuitReceivedFECNs.name: frCircuitReceivedFECNs
frCircuitReceivedFECNs.reference: Draft American National Standard T1.618-1991, Section 3.3.3
frCircuitReceivedFECNs.description: Number of frames received from the network in- dicating forward congestion since the virtual circuit was created.

frCircuitReceivedBECNs.name: frCircuitReceivedBECNs
frCircuitReceivedBECNs.reference: Draft American National Standard T1.618-1991, Section 3.3.4
frCircuitReceivedBECNs.description: Number of frames received from the network in- dicating backward congestion since the virtual circuit was created.

frCircuitSentFrames.name: frCircuitSentFrames
frCircuitSentFrames.description: The number of frames sent from this virtual circuit since it was created.

frCircuitSentOctets.name: frCircuitSentOctets
frCircuitSentOctets.description: The number of octets sent from this virtual circuit since it was created.

frCircuitReceivedFrames.name: frCircuitReceivedFrames
frCircuitReceivedFrames.description: Number of frames received over this virtual circuit since it was created.

frCircuitReceivedOctets.name: frCircuitReceivedOctets
frCircuitReceivedOctets.description: Number of octets received over this virtual circuit since it was created.

frCircuitCreationTime.name: frCircuitCreationTime
frCircuitCreationTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the virtual cir- cuit was created, whether by the Data Link Con- nection Management Interface or by a SetRe- quest.

frCircuitLastTimeChange.name: frCircuitLastTimeChange
frCircuitLastTimeChange.description: The value of sysUpTime when last there was a change in the virtual circuit state

frCircuitCommittedBurst.name: frCircuitCommittedBurst
frCircuitCommittedBurst.reference: Draft American National Standard T1.617-1991, Section 6.5.19
frCircuitCommittedBurst.description: This variable indicates the maximum amount of data, in bits, that the network agrees to transfer under normal conditions, during the measurement interval.

frCircuitExcessBurst.name: frCircuitExcessBurst
frCircuitExcessBurst.reference: Draft American National Standard T1.617-1991, Section 6.5.19
frCircuitExcessBurst.description: This variable indicates the maximum amount of uncommitted data bits that the network will at- tempt to deliver over the measurement interval. By default, if not configured when creating the entry, the Excess Information Burst Size is set to the value of ifSpeed.

frCircuitThroughput.name: frCircuitThroughput
frCircuitThroughput.reference: Draft American National Standard T1.617-1991, Section 6.5.19
frCircuitThroughput.description: Throughput is the average number of 'Frame Re- lay Information Field' bits transferred per second across a user network interface in one direction, measured over the measurement inter- val. If the configured committed burst rate and throughput are both non-zero, the measurement interval T=frCircuitCommittedBurst/frCircuitThroughput. If the configured committed burst rate and throughput are both zero, the measurement in- terval T=frCircuitExcessBurst/ifSpeed.

frErrTable.name: frErrTable
frErrTable.description: A table containing information about Errors on the Frame Relay interface.

frErrEntry.name: frErrEntry
frErrEntry.description: The error information for a single frame relay interface.

frErrIfIndex.name: frErrIfIndex
frErrIfIndex.description: The ifIndex Value of the corresponding ifEn- try.

frErrType.name: frErrType
frErrType.description: The type of error that was last seen on this interface.

frErrData.name: frErrData
frErrData.description: An octet string containing as much of the er- ror packet as possible. As a minimum, it must contain the Q.922 Address or as much as was delivered. It is desirable to include all in- formation up to the PDU.

frErrTime.name: frErrTime
frErrTime.description: The value of sysUpTime at which the error was detected.

frTrapState.name: frTrapState
frTrapState.description: This variable indicates whether the system produces the frDLCIStatusChange trap.

frDLCIStatusChange.name: frDLCIStatusChange
frDLCIStatusChange.description: This trap indicates that the indicated Virtual Circuit has changed state. It has either been created or invalidated, or has toggled between the active and inactive states.
